"'for I have found my sheep
which were lost."'

25
00:03:24,627 --> 00:03:27,829
I recollect the time Sam Harkness
lost his old sow.

26
00:03:29,096 --> 00:03:30,363
He come out one morning,

27
00:03:30,530 --> 00:03:33,198
The pen be busted down,
the sow was gone.

28
00:03:33,365 --> 00:03:35,766
Sam lit out after it to find it.

29
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:40,535
He had six or seven other pigs
that didn't run off.

30
00:03:40,969 --> 00:03:43,302
But did Sam get down
on his marrowbones,

31
00:03:43,469 --> 00:03:45,837
And thank the good Lord for that?

32
00:03:46,371 --> 00:03:48,339
No, siree, not Sam.

33
00:03:48,839 --> 00:03:51,006
He hunted high and low for that old...

34
